\sin^2 C & \cot C & 1
\end{vmatrix}
= \sin^2 A (\cot B - \cot C) - \cot A (\sin^2 B - \sin^2 C) + (\sin^2 B\cot C - \sin^2 C \cot B)
\]
Using the relationships $\cot x = \frac{\cos x}{\sin x}$ and $\sin^2x + \cos^2x = 1$, we can simplify each term:
\begin{align*}
\[\sin^2 A (\cot B - \cot C) &=\sin^2 A \left( \frac{\cos B}{\sin B}-\frac{\cos C}{\sin C}\right) \\ &= \sin^2 A \frac{\sin C \cos B - \cos C \sin B}{\sin B \sin C}\\ &=  \frac{\sin A}{\sin B\sin C} \sin( A-B)\cos( A+B)\\[3mm]
-\cot A (\sin^2 B - \sin^2 C) &= - \frac{\cos A}{\sin A}((\sin B + \cos B )(\sin B- \cos B ) - (\sin C + \cos C) (\sin C - \cos C))\\[3mm]
&= - \frac{\cos A}{\sin A} ( \sin^2 B - \cos^2 B- \sin^2 C + \cos^2 C)  \\ &=- \frac{\cos A}{\sin A} (\sin(B-C)(\sin B + \sin C) )\\ & = -\frac{ \cos A (\sin B + \sin C)(-\sin (B-C) )}{\sin A}\\ & =  \frac{\cos A (\sin B + \sin C) \sin (C-B) }{ \sin A}\\[3mm]
\pm (\sin^2 B\cot C - \sin^2 C \cot B)&= \sin^2B  \frac{\cos C}{\sin C}- \sin^2 C \frac{\cos B}{\sin B}  \\ & =  \frac{\sin B)(\cos B(\sin^2 B)- \sin C (\cos B \sin^2 C)}{\sin B\sin C} \\ & =   \frac{\sin B)(\sin B\cos B(\sin^2 B+\sin^2 C -\sin^2 C)}{\sin C (sin B\sin C)} \\
& = \frac{\sin B ( \sin^2 B\cos B)}{\sin C ( \sin C)}
\end{align*}
Therefore, combining all the simplified terms together, we get:
\[
\begin{vmatrix}
