= \sin A\cos B \sin(C-B)+ \frac{\cos A (\sin B + \sin C) \sin(C-B) }{ \sin A }   -\frac{\sin B (\sin B\cos B (\sin^2 B+\sin^2 C -\sin^2 C))}{\sin C ( \sin C)}
\]
Since $\sin(C-B) = -\sin(B-C),$  we get:
